'''Ralph Brown''' (born [[June 18]], [[1950s#1957|1957]]) is an English actor who played [[Ric Olié]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']].

Brown was born in [[Wikipedia:Cambridgeshire|Cambridgeshire]], England on [[June 18]], [[1950s#1957|1957]]. Though he claims to be an "untrained actor", Brown has had nearly sixty roles on television and in films since [[1982]]. These include "Danny the Drug Dealer" in [[Wikipedia:Withnail and I|''Withnail and I'']], the security guard Aaron in [[Wikipedia:Alien³|''Alien³'']], and the eccentric roadie Del Preston in [[Wikipedia:Wayne's World 2|''Wayne's World 2'']]. He also wrote, produced, and acted in the [[2001]] film ''{{IMDb|title/tt0185542|New Year's Day}}

In addition to his acting, Brown is a musician, who plays alto saxophone and piano. He is currently part of a [[Wikipedia:Brighton|Brighton, England]]-based [[Wikipedia:The Beach Boys|Beach Boys]] tribute band called "The Brighton Beach Boys."

